# sdist contents. Both distributions now carry the full canonical docs corpus (docs/):
# the WHEEL carries it because a rendered engine error resolves its audit_code / rule_id
# LOCALLY against the docs shipped in the package (RFC-9457 type = about:blank, no web URI —
# docs/components/error-channel/reference.md, the `type` row), so the corpus must ride the
# installed package. Because docs/ lives outside the importable package (src/conjured/),
# package-data cannot reach it; the wheel force-includes it via setup.py's custom build_py
# (which copies docs/ into the package build tree — same prunes as below). The sdist carries
# it via the `graft docs` here, alongside the shipping tools and the test suite — the canon
# IS the product's spec, so the source distribution ships it too.
#
# LICENSE, NOTICE, README.md, and pyproject.toml are included automatically (license-files
# + readme metadata); the grafts below add the non-package trees setuptools would not
# otherwise collect. (The wheel's docs copy is setup.py's job, not this file's — MANIFEST.in
# governs the sdist only.)

graft docs
graft tools
graft tests

# Never ship build/cache detritus. `prune` is path-relative to the sdist root, so the
# grafted trees need their own prunes — a nested cache (e.g. tools/.pytest_cache, left by
# running the tools' test suite) is NOT reached by the root-level prune.
global-exclude __pycache__ *.py[cod] *.so
prune docs/_build
prune .pytest_cache
prune tools/.pytest_cache
prune tests/.pytest_cache
prune .deepeval

include CHANGELOG.md
